.TH COMMANDSOURCE 1 "January 2026" "commandsource" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
commandsource \- simple command console (Node.js)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B commandsource
[\fB--run\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB--prompt\fR \fITEXT\fR] [\fB--no-prompt\fR] [\fB--help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
commandsource is a small interactive command console ported from a C implementation.
It provides a minimal prompt, a `help` command, and clean shutdown behavior.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h , " " --help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.BR --run " " N
Exit after N commands have been processed.
.TP
.BR --prompt " " TEXT
Set the prompt string (default: "> ").
.TP
.BR --no-prompt
Disable prompt output (useful when piping input).

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B help [command]
List available commands or show a single command.
.TP
.B quit
Exit the console.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run interactively:
.IP
.nf
commandsource
.fi
Pipe commands and exit after 3 lines:
.IP
.nf
printf "help\nhelp quit\nquit\n" | commandsource --no-prompt --run 3
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on normal exit, non-zero on internal error.
